ck;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/3c3c8242-4987-4792-a6a6-73c7a1353432/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/IMG_6484.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" width="1496" height="1995" natural-width="1496" natural-height="1995"></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1661521441708" class="gf_row gf_gs-spacing-xl-m-top gf_row-gap-20" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1661521441708" data-extraclass="" data-row-gap="20px" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1660936798945" data-id="1660936798945"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1661521441693" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1661521441693" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/1f6f32f5-a8f0-4d7f-a75f-c33ff6c2b565/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Frame%2068.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="302" height="302" data-width="10%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="302" natural-height="302"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1661521441816" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1661521441816"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h1 class="gf_gs_ct">3. Regular Exercise</h1></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1661521441742" class="element-wrap gf_gs-spacing-lg-m-top" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1661521441742"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs_ct gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Try to get 150 min to 300 min a week of moderately intense exercise. Perform both aerobic (cardio) and anaerobic (resistance) exercises. One example includes lifting weights 4 days per week and walking / running on the treadmill 3 days per week.⁵</p></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1661521501637" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-20 gf_gs-spacing-158073-m-top" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1661521501637" data-extraclass="" data-row-gap="20px" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1660936798945" data-id="1660936798945"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1661528195038" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1661528195038" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/dfc43d23-5c9e-44e1-93d8-6b75acd93339/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/261137197_967253060570612_60957166496993_n.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1080" height="1350" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1080" natural-height="1350"></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1661528175028" data-id="1661528175028"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1661521501679" class="element-wrap gf_gs-spacing-158073-m-top" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1661521501679" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/1f6f32f5-a8f0-4d7f-a75f-c33ff6c2b565/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Frame%2068.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="302" height="302" data-width="10%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="302" natural-height="302"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1661521501746" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1661521501746"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h1 class="gf_gs_ct">4. Drink Plenty of WATER</h1></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1661521501698" class="element-wrap gf_gs-spacing-lg-m-top" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1661521501698"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs_ct gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Consume 64-128 oz of water per day. This only includes water and not other liquids like soda or fruit juice. Benefits of drinking water include delivery of nutrients to cells, flushing bacteria from bladder, aiding digestion, regulating heart rate and blood pressure, cushioning joints, maintaining body temperature, and regulating electrolyte balance.⁶</p></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1661521638493" class="gf_row gf_gs-spacing-xl-m-top gf_row-gap-20" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1661521638493" data-extraclass="" data-row-gap="20px" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1660936798945" data-id="1660936798945"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1